extends _layout

block body
  #top
    a.github(href='https://github.com/dawson-org/dawson-cli')
      img(src='img/GitHub-Mark-Light-64px.png')
    .container
      .spacer-100
      img.logo(src='img/dawson-logo@2x-white.png' alt='dawson | a serverless framework for Node.js on AWS')
      h1 a serverless framework for Node.js on AWS
      .spacer-50

      .terminal-window
        .bar
          .btn
        .body
          pre
            .comment # installing dawson globally
            .prompt
              | $&nbsp;
              span.command npm install -g dawson
            .comment # loading your AWS credentials
            .prompt
              | $&nbsp;
              span.command source .env
            .comment # deploy your app
            .prompt
              | $&nbsp;
              span.command dawson deploy
              //- span.pulse _
      
      .spacer-20
      a.pure-button.pure-button-negative(href='docs.html')
        span View full documentation
      .spacer-100

  #preview
    .container
      .spacer-50
      .padding

        .intro
          :markdown-it(breaks=true linkify=true)

            dawson is a [serverless](https://auth0.com/blog/what-is-serverless/) web framework for Node.js on AWS. dawson uses [AWS CloudFormation](https://aws.amazon.com/cloudformation/), [Amazon CloudFront](https://aws.amazon.com/cloudfront/), [Amazon API Gateway](https://aws.amazon.com/apigateway/) and  [AWS Lambda](https://aws.amazon.com/lambda/) to deploy the backend code and to manage the infrastructure for you. 

        .spacer-50

        .others
          .text-center.for-me
            h1 Is dawson for me?
            .pure-g
              .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-3
                .padding
                  img(src='img/icon-code-100.png')
                  h3 I'm building a single-page app/website with a backend
              .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-3
                .padding
                  img(src='img/icon-api-100.png')
                  h3 I'm building an API
              .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-3
                .padding
                  img(src='img/icon-website-100.png')
                  h3 I'm building a server-rendered app/website

          .spacer-50

          :markdown-it(breaks=true linkify=true html=true)
            The main goal of dawson is to be a zero-configuration yet fully extensible *[backend]* web framework for building web apps on AWS. You should be able to start using dawson without creating any configuration file and with only a basic knowledge of Amazon Web Services.

            <div class="spacer-10"></div>

            ```js
            // api.js
            export function greet (event) {
                const name = event.params.path.name
                return `Hello ${name}, you look awesome!`
            }
            greet.api = {
                path: 'greet/{name}'
            }
            ```
            ```bash
            $ # we strongly recommend to read this guide
            $ #     before getting your hands dirty     
            $ npm install -g dawson
            $ export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=... AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=... AWS_REGION=...
            $ dawson deploy


          .spacer-10
          .text-center
            a.pure-button(href='docs.html')
              span View full documentation

    .spacer-50


